       Name: Cognitive Pressure
       Kind: Spell
     Target: TAR_CHAR_OFFENSIVE
   Position: POS_FIGHTING
   Min Mana: 8
 Wait Beats: 12
 Can Learn: FALSE
Noun Damage: cognitive pressure
   Wear-Off: !Cognitive Pressure!
Acquisition:
   - Psionicist: level 1
Description:
   Cognitive Pressure is the first technique in Psionicist training: focused
   will directed at a surface cognitive pattern, pressing against it until
   the subject flinches. In the tradition's mainstream doctrine this is
   explicitly defensive in origin — taught as a way to interrupt a threat,
   not pursue one. The technique matters more than the force it delivers.

   Damage: 2d4 + level/4, mental elemental. A successful save halves damage.
   Has no effect on mindless targets (ACT_NOMIND). Cannot be used on self.
   Mana cost: 8. Available automatically at level 1.

   Psionicists who need heavier mental offense should advance to Mind Flail
   (level 4), which does not scale with level but applies tiered damage at
   level thresholds.
